components.name: Text Input
components.description:
Allows the user to input a text (potentially with template variables) that can be used in other downstream components.
    Inputs:
      `Input` (str): The text to output.
    Output (str): The inputted text.

inputs.value: The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog

output.value: The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog

components.label: TEXTINPUT-0

components.name: Azure Open AI vectorizer
components.description:
Encodes inputted texts as numerical vectors (embeddings) using Azure OpenAI models.
    Input (List[str]): A list of texts to encode. If needed, the list can be inputted manually by the user.
    Output (List[Dict]): A list of dictionaries -- one for each text in the input. Each dictionary contains the key `text` (str) mapped to the original text (str), and the key `embeddings` (str) mapped to the embedding (List[Union[float, int]]).

value: The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog

value.text: The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog

components.label: AZUREOPENAIVECTORIZER-1
